Here I will explain how to create an extremely simple Register page for new people to PHP

<blockquote>Without encryption/hashing it is worth nothing. If you are teaching someone something, teach them the good way.</blockquote> 
Added MD5 hashing...

to begin start by declaring some variables(vars)...
<blockquote><?php include("database.php"); ?>
<?php
//vars
$email = strtolower(strip_tags($_POST ['email'])); //makes all letters lower
$username = ucwords(strip_tags($_POST ['uname']));//capitalize first letter in each word (John Doe)
$pass1 = strip_tags($_POST ['pass1']);//strip tags (<html>)
$pass2 =strip_tags($_POST ['pass2']); 
$pass3 = md5($pass1);//Encrypt the password
$b = $_POST['button'];//if pushed
?></blockquote>

Now we start with the HTML...
<blockquote><?php echo"
<form action='(documentname.php)' method='POST'>//POST makes it not visible in browser
Email: <input type='text' name='email'>
Username: <input type='text' name='username'>
Password: <input type='password' name='pass1'>
Repeat: <input type='password' name='pass2'>
<input type='submit' name='button' value='Register'>
</form>";</blockquote>

Now the html is done, we have to actually write out to see if the user filled this form out correctly...(PUT THIS BEFORE THE REGISTER FIELD IN THE .PHP DOCUMENT)

<blockquote>$connect = mysql_connect("localhost","root","");
mysql_select_db("users");//connects to your database
if($b)//if button is pressed
{
